3rd annual National Day for Truth and Reconciliation. We attended todays event at the old Lejac Residential School site which operated from 1922 to 1976. It is a heavy day but also has its good parts too. Got to see a lot of good people that gathered from all over and a lot of my fam were in attendance as well. Seeing the new generations of children take in the day with smiles and laughter helped cap it off.

Playing in a little alumni game tonight in PG!

Such a great time had at our alumni game Tuesday night. 

It was us old guys vs the young bucks and we just barely squeezed out the W lol. 

Hard to believe this was 17 years ago. Was so good to see former teammates and friends. All of us no longer young teenage boys but now men with careers, wives, kids, etc. Looking back now this was definitely one of the most fun years I’ve had in hockey. 

I owe a lot to this team. They gave me a chance to crack the squad despite playing single A minor hockey in Fraser Lake. Actually, 3 of us Fraser Lake Hawks made the team that year. 2 from Burns Lake. And 1 from Fort. I was 15 when I moved to PG with those guys, which made living away from home a bit easier. And it was nice to be teammates with our minor hockey rivals from those other towns for once as we were always beating each other up on the ice in the years prior lol. Now we could do that together vs all those lower mainland teams. 

We had a pretty successful year after the team was made. Season champs then a loss in the  final round of playoffs. The year after I went to play for the Spruce Kings but a lot of these guys stayed behind and finished the job the following year and won it all. I was super proud of them for getting that done. 

17 years and 7 more teams later I get to go back pretty darn close to the start of it all. Looking forward to the next one!
